  "texts": [
    "An isomorphism of twisted principal N-bundles is a bundle map which acts on the fibres by affine transformations.If f: M → M ′ is an isomorphism of twisted principal bundles covering f: B → B ′, then it can be written in appropriate trivialisations U i × N, U ′ j × N as f (u, n) = ( f (u), φ u (n)) for some φ: U i → Aut(N).",
    "2.2.The adjoint bundle and connections on twisted principal bundles.",
    "Recall that the adjoint bundle of a principal N-bundle is the associated bundle for the adjoint representation Ad: N → GL(𝔫), obtained by composing the transition functions with Ad.",
    "Associated to any twisted principal bundle π: M → B there is an analogous construction: a Lie algebra bundle adM → B, also called the adjoint bundle.To define it, given a bundle atlas {U i × N} for π: M → B, we let U i × 𝔫 be the vector bundle over U i whose sections are the vertical right-invariant fields in U i × N. Composing the transition functions of {U i × N} with the map(8) Aut(N) ⋉ N → Aut(𝔫), (φ, n) → dφ e • Ad(n)we obtain the data to define a vector bundle adM over B.",
    "Since the structure group is contained in Aut(𝔫), the fibres of adM have a well-defined Lie algebra structure."
  ],
